WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:06.458
[NOIR FILM ON TV]

00:10.500 --> 00:14.542
[IMITATING DARTH VADER]
Luke, I am your father.

00:14.542 --> 00:15.750
Pacey?

00:15.750 --> 00:17.667
You're monopolizing
what's passing for a breeze.

00:17.667 --> 00:21.000
Ahh. Dawson,
this is gonna go down

00:21.000 --> 00:23.875
as one of the most
abysmal movie nights ever.

00:23.875 --> 00:26.166
[LAUGHS]
Care to elaborate?

00:26.166 --> 00:27.959
Well, look around you,
my friend.

00:27.959 --> 00:29.291
We're two happening
young guys

00:29.291 --> 00:30.542
in the prime
of our lives,

00:30.542 --> 00:31.834
who can't find
anything better to do

00:31.834 --> 00:33.375
than sit in some
sweat box

00:33.375 --> 00:35.792
in the middle of
an armpit-staining Indian Summer

00:35.792 --> 00:36.959
and watch old movies.

00:37.208 --> 00:38.708
I mean, correct me
if I'm wrong, Dawson,

00:38.708 --> 00:39.708
but didn't we
used to have

00:39.708 --> 00:41.250
a couple of really cute
girlfriends?

00:41.500 --> 00:42.750
It was a long time
ago, Pace,

00:42.750 --> 00:44.375
in a galaxy far,
far away.

00:44.375 --> 00:46.792
-[SIGHS]
-DAWSON: God...

00:47.291 --> 00:49.375
I can't wrap my head
around this film noir stuff

00:49.375 --> 00:50.625
which is making it
really difficult

00:50.625 --> 00:51.834
to turn out
a paper on it.

00:51.834 --> 00:53.083
[LAUGHS]
Well, of course you can't

00:53.083 --> 00:54.625
wrap your head
around it, Dawson.

00:55.083 --> 00:56.000
Excuse me?

00:56.375 --> 00:58.500
Well, what we're watching here
is the cinema of cynicism.

00:58.875 --> 01:00.708
No self-respecting
son of Spielberg

01:00.708 --> 01:03.083
would feel comfortable
in a morally ambiguous world

01:03.083 --> 01:04.959
populated with
hard-boiled antiheroes

01:04.959 --> 01:06.792
and duplicitous
femme fatales.

01:06.792 --> 01:08.125
You know what?
Could we just reschedule

01:08.125 --> 01:09.208
this verbal joust, Pace?

01:09.208 --> 01:10.834
It's a little too hot
for spiky repartee.

01:10.834 --> 01:13.083
[LAUGHS]
Mmm.

01:14.667 --> 01:15.875
But this, right here?

01:15.875 --> 01:18.917
This is celluloid a fellow
like me can relate to.

01:19.208 --> 01:20.291
Pacey Witter is nothing

01:20.291 --> 01:22.125
if not the walking,
talking embodiment

01:22.125 --> 01:23.708
of the fallible
protagonist.

01:24.291 --> 01:27.208
Ok, Johnny Anti-Hero,
explain to me this,

01:27.458 --> 01:29.417
how can this guy not know
[LAUGHS]

01:29.417 --> 01:30.792
that this woman
is setting him up

01:30.792 --> 01:32.208
for a fall of epic proportions?

01:32.667 --> 01:35.708
Because, Dawson,
not all of us are as immune

01:35.708 --> 01:37.708
to the lure of sex
as you are.

01:37.708 --> 01:38.875
I mean, not all of us would opt

01:38.875 --> 01:41.333
for the warm and fuzzy
emotional connections

01:41.333 --> 01:44.458
over those of, let's say,
a more physical nature.

01:44.458 --> 01:45.417
You know what I mean?

01:45.750 --> 01:47.291
Most of us
are just big, dumb guys

01:47.291 --> 01:48.583
happy to sell our souls

01:48.583 --> 01:51.458
for the slimmest chance
of gettin' some.

01:51.458 --> 01:53.333
[LAUGHS]
Can I quote you on that?

01:53.333 --> 01:55.166
Oh, yeah. Witter, two "T's."

01:56.417 --> 01:57.417
Fun time's over.

01:57.417 --> 01:58.917
All this rapid-fire
deconstruction

01:58.917 --> 02:00.417
is making me weary, Leery.

02:00.834 --> 02:02.834
I think I shall retire
to cooler climes,

02:03.166 --> 02:06.875
namely, the air-conditioned
interior of my pop's squad car.

02:07.375 --> 02:08.625
Good night, Pace.

02:08.625 --> 02:10.291
Mm-hmm.

02:10.291 --> 02:11.500
[SIGHS]

02:16.583 --> 02:17.792
[MUTES TV]

02:18.458 --> 02:21.250
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]
-[SIGHS]

02:22.417 --> 02:25.959
[TIRES ON DIRT ROAD]

02:27.041 --> 02:29.083
♪ [MYSTERIOUS MUSIC] ♪

02:31.792 --> 02:34.333
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]
-[DIALING PHONE]

02:36.250 --> 02:37.708
OPERATOR: Capeside Police?

02:38.000 --> 02:40.291
Yeah, I'd like to report
a possible robbery.

02:40.875 --> 02:44.166
♪ [NOIR SAXOPHONE MUSIC] ♪

02:54.166 --> 02:55.417
[THUD]

02:59.625 --> 03:01.083
Hey, Dawson.

03:04.166 --> 03:08.291
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

03:51.875 --> 03:53.542
Ok, explanation.

03:53.542 --> 03:54.667
Ouch!

03:55.250 --> 03:56.583
Thanks to your
nosy neighbor antics

03:56.583 --> 03:59.250
out there, Dawson,
I fell down and went boom.

03:59.250 --> 04:01.750
-Kiss and make better?
-Eve, I just called the police.

04:01.750 --> 04:03.041
They're gonna be here
any minute.

04:03.500 --> 04:05.750
[SIGHS]
Ok, I'll spill.

04:06.500 --> 04:08.542
We didn't want you to find out
this way, Dawson,

04:08.542 --> 04:10.917
but me and Jen?
We're having ourselves

04:10.917 --> 04:12.583
quite the torrid little affair.

04:13.250 --> 04:15.250
Sleepovers, late night
pillow fights,

04:15.708 --> 04:18.083
brushing each other's hair,
tickling each other's arms,

04:18.834 --> 04:20.250
all that groovy stuff
we girls do

04:20.250 --> 04:22.208
in pretty pink rooms,
behind closed doors.

04:22.208 --> 04:24.166
Eve, there was a breaking,
there was an entering,

04:24.166 --> 04:25.083
and there was a flashlight.

04:25.083 --> 04:26.500
All that's missing
is a ski mask.

04:26.792 --> 04:28.083
Good God.

04:28.083 --> 04:30.041
Not even the suggestion
of teen lesbianism

04:30.041 --> 04:31.458
can get you off my case.

04:32.583 --> 04:36.250
Can we just,
like, make out or something?

04:36.625 --> 04:38.083
Let me kiss
all your queries away.

04:38.083 --> 04:39.542
Look, Eve, either you tell me
your version,

04:39.542 --> 04:40.750
or I tell the police mine.

04:40.750 --> 04:44.750
Fine. Do what your big,
bleeding heart wants, Dawson,

04:45.417 --> 04:47.458
but here's a filthy
4-letter word for you,

04:47.458 --> 04:48.834
and don't you dare blush.

04:49.417 --> 04:51.417
P-S-A-T, baby.

04:52.208 --> 04:53.542
Don't you remember
where you were

04:53.542 --> 04:57.500
when the cataclysmic PSAT
scandal of '99 went down?

04:57.792 --> 04:58.667
I for sure do.

04:58.667 --> 05:00.291
Is that some sort
of threat, Eve?

05:00.542 --> 05:01.417
Because might I remind you,

05:01.667 --> 05:02.959
you're the one that actually
stole the test.

05:03.417 --> 05:04.959
And may I remind you
that you're the one

05:04.959 --> 05:07.375
who gladly accepted
my trial offer?

05:07.375 --> 05:10.083
So feel free to get
all boy-scouty on me, Dawson,

05:10.667 --> 05:11.667
but you should know

05:11.959 --> 05:13.667
I'd get quite the perverse
little thrill

05:13.667 --> 05:15.917
out of making things profoundly
uncomfortable

05:15.917 --> 05:16.834
for you and the rest

05:16.834 --> 05:18.417
of the "Sweet Valley
High" extras

05:18.417 --> 05:19.834
you call your friends?

05:20.125 --> 05:22.333
♪ [NOIR SAXOPHONE MUSIC] ♪

05:25.333 --> 05:26.291
[SIGHS]

05:26.291 --> 05:27.834
[KNOCKING]

05:31.125 --> 05:33.333
Doug, hi.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.667
Uh, my sincerest
apologies.

05:35.667 --> 05:38.417
I-- I thought I saw
something next door,

05:38.417 --> 05:41.125
but it was actually
just, uh, Jen,

05:41.125 --> 05:42.166
uh, sneaking
in the window

05:42.166 --> 05:44.750
so as not to disturb Grams.

05:46.834 --> 05:48.291
You sure about that, Dawson?

05:49.125 --> 05:51.542
Yeah. yeah, just...

05:52.542 --> 05:53.625
Ok, then.

05:54.083 --> 05:56.834
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]
-[FROGS CROAKING]

06:00.542 --> 06:01.834
[DOOR CLOSES]

06:04.542 --> 06:07.875
♪ [NOIR SAXOPHONE MUSIC] ♪

06:18.542 --> 06:21.125
You know, I saw this article
in this magazine once,

06:21.834 --> 06:23.500
where they put this thing
up in the sky,

06:23.500 --> 06:24.875
so that the kids
studying astronomy

06:24.875 --> 06:27.041
could track something
during the night,

06:27.041 --> 06:30.750
and I think that is it ri--
or maybe that's it.

06:31.667 --> 06:33.875
Wait. You, you expect me
to believe there's some sort

06:33.875 --> 06:36.542
of giant disco ball
orbiting the earth?

06:36.917 --> 06:40.041
Ok, when you put it like that,
it sounds kind of stupid.

06:40.333 --> 06:42.625
Maybe we should start thinking
about getting out of here.

06:42.625 --> 06:45.041
I don't think so.
Not before the main event.

06:45.041 --> 06:48.417
Come on, we've got the stars,
we've got the moonlight.

06:49.208 --> 06:50.125
It's perfect.

06:50.417 --> 06:52.750
[LAUGHS]
Yeah. Lying in the grass,

06:52.750 --> 06:55.542
on a hot Indian Summer night
with your gay best friend.

06:55.542 --> 06:57.208
That's your definition
of perfect?

06:57.750 --> 06:59.083
A girl could do a lot worse.

06:59.417 --> 07:01.291
Come on, Jen,
I know you too well.

07:01.583 --> 07:03.291
You can't tell me
there isn't someone else

07:03.291 --> 07:05.041
that you'd rather be
stargazing with.

07:06.166 --> 07:07.500
Ok, you got me.

07:08.250 --> 07:09.166
Matt Damon.

07:09.166 --> 07:11.333
[LAUGHS]
Yeah, right.

07:11.333 --> 07:12.792
What, you don't approve?

07:12.792 --> 07:14.542
All right, I'll have to go
with Ben Affleck, then.

07:14.542 --> 07:17.625
Well, he's got that scruffy,
indie cred appeal.

07:19.333 --> 07:21.083
-Well?
-No comment.

07:21.417 --> 07:23.291
Besides, I was talking
more about the realm

07:23.291 --> 07:25.625
of the, oh, say possible?
Henry, for instance?

07:26.166 --> 07:27.708
Henry, for instance?

07:28.667 --> 07:29.792
The freshman?

07:29.792 --> 07:32.792
Yeah, the guy paid
$500 bucks just to kiss you.

07:32.792 --> 07:34.708
You've got to admit,
that's kind of sweet.

07:35.250 --> 07:37.417
Jack, Jack, Jack,
my naive little pet,

07:37.417 --> 07:39.792
it's the sweet ones
that you have to watch out for.

07:40.417 --> 07:41.959
They'll run over you
like a Mac Truck.

07:42.625 --> 07:45.333
Yeah, well, Henry's harmless.
Besides, he worships you.

07:45.792 --> 07:46.792
He's a teenage boy.

07:46.792 --> 07:48.792
He'd worship anything
in a wonder bra.

07:48.792 --> 07:49.792
[LAUGHS]

07:49.792 --> 07:50.625
Besides,

07:51.041 --> 07:52.834
I'm already sleeping
with the best looking guy

07:52.834 --> 07:54.083
on the football team.

07:56.959 --> 07:59.208
And best friends are nothing
to sneeze at.

08:01.959 --> 08:04.500
God, I remember when I first met
Joey and Dawson.

08:06.458 --> 08:08.458
I was so envious
of what they had,

08:08.458 --> 08:09.750
all that history.

08:11.375 --> 08:15.375
Then that whole boyfriend-
girlfriend thing kicked in.

08:16.542 --> 08:18.250
See, that's what's
so great about us.

08:18.792 --> 08:20.917
Sex will never come
between you and me.

08:20.917 --> 08:22.250
-[SIGHS]
-[WATER SPRAYS]

08:22.250 --> 08:25.166
Oh, no! Oh, God, no!

08:25.500 --> 08:29.458
No! Get the shoes!
Get the shoes!

08:30.458 --> 08:32.125
-No, wait, wait.
-Get the shoes!

08:32.125 --> 08:33.041
I got them.

08:34.000 --> 08:35.166
[SCREAMS]

08:35.750 --> 08:36.625
[LAUGHS]

08:37.500 --> 08:39.500
Not so tough now,
are you, homecoming queen?

08:39.500 --> 08:40.500
Aah!

08:41.457 --> 08:44.207
Look at you. And you said
that this wasn't perfect.

08:44.959 --> 08:47.625
♪ [MUSIC] ♪

09:15.083 --> 09:16.708
Come on, Potter,
take a break.

09:16.708 --> 09:19.166
-Hydrate yourself.
-No thanks, I'm fine.

09:19.458 --> 09:20.250
I insist.

09:20.542 --> 09:21.834
It would look very bad
for the Logan family

09:21.834 --> 09:23.667
if you got heatstroke
and died on them.

09:24.250 --> 09:25.917
It's nice to know you care.

09:30.375 --> 09:33.125
How can it possibly be this hot
at 7:30 in the morning?

09:33.875 --> 09:35.417
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

09:40.125 --> 09:42.959
Is this gonna offend
your delicate sensibilities?

09:44.250 --> 09:46.208
I'll probably swoon
with excitement,

09:47.000 --> 09:48.750
but seeing as though
I need this job

09:48.750 --> 09:50.250
to support my sister
and nephew,

09:50.500 --> 09:52.792
I will just choose
to look the other way.

09:55.333 --> 09:57.208
So, uh, Potter,
what do you say?

09:57.542 --> 09:59.041
You and me at the movies
tonight?

09:59.792 --> 10:01.667
Oh, joy. Is this
the part of our workday

10:01.667 --> 10:02.917
where you
get inappropriate?

10:03.208 --> 10:04.792
That depends on what
your answer is.

10:05.125 --> 10:09.166
My answer is, ask me again
in 2 years, when I am legal.

10:09.166 --> 10:11.458
You watch, Potter.
Some other lucky little lady's

10:11.458 --> 10:12.583
gonna take me up on this offer,

10:12.583 --> 10:13.959
and you're gonna
be green with envy.

10:16.417 --> 10:18.708
I think I can live
with that possibility.

10:21.250 --> 10:22.208
[WATER SPRAYS]

10:22.208 --> 10:24.708
-Stop it! Stop!
-Why? It's just water.

10:24.959 --> 10:26.667
Stop it! Stop it!

10:26.667 --> 10:27.959
Come on. what, are
all teenage girls

10:27.959 --> 10:29.041
as uptight as you?

10:29.625 --> 10:31.667
No, just the ones
with half a brain.

10:32.125 --> 10:35.333
♪ [MUSIC] ♪

10:36.959 --> 10:39.041
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

10:44.959 --> 10:46.959
You say this girl
is a very close friend?

10:46.959 --> 10:48.291
Uh, very close, yes.

10:48.625 --> 10:50.291
And yet, you don't have
the slightest idea

10:50.291 --> 10:51.417
where she lives?

10:51.792 --> 10:54.125
Oh, I'm sorry, kid.
We're closed.

10:54.500 --> 10:57.375
I'm not here for
the titillations, sir.

10:57.375 --> 10:59.333
I'm actually looking for a girl
I go to school with.

10:59.333 --> 11:00.417
She used to work here.

11:01.375 --> 11:02.333
What's the name?

11:02.333 --> 11:04.417
Uh, Whitman.
Eve Whitman.

11:04.417 --> 11:06.875
She's, a tall,
leggy blonde

11:06.875 --> 11:09.333
genetically engineered
to corrupt the male species?

11:09.333 --> 11:10.417
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

11:10.417 --> 11:12.000
Sorry to be the bearer
of bad news, young man,

11:12.000 --> 11:14.000
but I think somebody's
playing games with you.

11:14.000 --> 11:14.875
What do you mean?

11:14.875 --> 11:17.291
-Kid, how old are you, 16?
-Yeah.

11:17.291 --> 11:19.708
Now, if you're 16,
that means you're underage,

11:19.708 --> 11:21.333
and if you're underage,
you would never

11:21.333 --> 11:22.792
be permitted
into my establishment.

11:22.792 --> 11:24.834
And if you're going to school
with one of my girls,

11:24.834 --> 11:26.625
that means she would
be underage as well.

11:26.625 --> 11:30.834
So, what can we take away
from today's tutorial, huh?

11:31.458 --> 11:33.959
There is not, there was not,
there never has been

11:33.959 --> 11:36.458
an Eve Whitman
enrolled at Capeside High.

11:42.625 --> 11:43.750
-[BELL RINGS]
-Come on, come on.

11:43.750 --> 11:44.667
Let's go, already.

11:44.959 --> 11:46.667
I don't see why we have
to practice in this heat.

11:46.917 --> 11:47.667
It's gotta violate,

11:47.917 --> 11:49.333
like, a thousand
child endangerment laws.

11:49.625 --> 11:51.667
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Talk to the hand.

11:51.667 --> 11:53.125
Listen, we're late.

11:53.125 --> 11:55.750
Big, bad Mitch
is gonna kick our--

11:55.750 --> 11:57.542
-Kick our what?
-Don't look.

11:58.041 --> 12:00.083
She's coming.
She's coming this way.

12:00.083 --> 12:01.041
Just act normal.

12:01.417 --> 12:04.542
Henry, when she comes over here,
just ask her out already, ok,

12:04.542 --> 12:06.834
-because this is ridiculous.
-It's not that easy, ok?

12:06.834 --> 12:08.834
You don't know how hard it is
for me to talk to her.

12:08.834 --> 12:09.834
I mean, look at her.

12:09.834 --> 12:13.000
Look, she's, like,
this perfect thing.

12:13.542 --> 12:14.625
You think
she looks good in that,

12:14.625 --> 12:16.208
you should see her in a towel.

12:16.625 --> 12:18.708
Mmm, boys, do I have good news.

12:18.708 --> 12:20.708
The ice cream man?
Right outside.

12:21.208 --> 12:23.083
-You want a lick?
-Uh, no thanks.

12:23.375 --> 12:24.417
Henry?

12:24.875 --> 12:27.792
Uh...uh...

12:31.583 --> 12:33.041
Mmm-mmm, no?

12:34.583 --> 12:37.625
Ok, suit yourself.
I'll see you later?

12:37.625 --> 12:39.208
-Later.
-Bye, Henry.

12:40.125 --> 12:42.250
Um...oh.

12:42.750 --> 12:45.000
You see? You see
what happens to me?

12:45.000 --> 12:46.583
Why I can't ask her out?

12:46.583 --> 12:48.000
She gets within 3 feet of me,

12:48.000 --> 12:50.208
and it's like my hard drive
crashes.

12:50.834 --> 12:51.917
I go pre-verbal.

12:52.208 --> 12:54.500
Probably if I asked her out,
I'd hurl all over her

12:54.500 --> 12:56.125
like that little kid
in South Park.

12:56.417 --> 13:00.166
Ok, so what if you didn't
have to ask her out?

13:01.250 --> 13:02.500
You mean, like,
you could get her

13:02.500 --> 13:03.625
to ask me out?

13:03.625 --> 13:05.917
I'm so down with
that feminist stuff.

13:06.208 --> 13:08.166
Henry, I'm good,
but I'm not that good.

13:08.166 --> 13:10.917
No, what if
your first date was like,

13:10.917 --> 13:14.625
um, was like kismet?
You know, like fate?

13:15.166 --> 13:16.458
Two people just happening to be

13:16.458 --> 13:20.208
at the exact same place,
at the exact same time.

13:23.083 --> 13:24.458
[BELL RINGS]

13:26.250 --> 13:28.041
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

13:32.542 --> 13:34.667
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

13:36.625 --> 13:37.959
Dawson Leery.

13:39.458 --> 13:41.542
How are things that go bump
in the night?

13:41.959 --> 13:43.667
Deputy Witter.
I was wondering

13:43.667 --> 13:45.208
if I could pose
a hypothetical?

13:45.208 --> 13:46.125
Pose away.

13:46.125 --> 13:47.792
Well, I'm working on
a screenplay.

13:47.792 --> 13:49.959
It's a film noir piece
with a cop protagonist.

13:49.959 --> 13:51.458
I was wondering
if I could pick your brain

13:51.458 --> 13:52.542
on a few story points.

13:52.542 --> 13:53.667
How can I help?

13:53.667 --> 13:54.917
Uh, well, I could
use some help

13:54.917 --> 13:56.375
with procedure,
actually, um,

13:56.875 --> 13:58.750
I'm stuck on the part
where the hero

13:58.750 --> 14:00.333
is trying to track down
the femme fatale

14:00.333 --> 14:01.875
who's all but disappeared
at this point.

14:02.291 --> 14:05.166
Now, how would a law enforcement
professional such as yourself,

14:05.166 --> 14:07.291
go about finding someone
who doesn't want to be found?

14:07.291 --> 14:09.417
Well, that's a good
question, Dawson.

14:09.417 --> 14:11.417
Now, part of police work

14:11.917 --> 14:14.959
is knowing who your enemy is.
So, let me as you this,

14:16.083 --> 14:19.166
-Who is this girl?
-She's kind of a lost soul.

14:19.583 --> 14:21.667
I mean, she comes off
like sort of a wild child,

14:21.667 --> 14:23.000
but I think there's
something really sweet

14:23.000 --> 14:24.875
and vulnerable underneath
all her posturing.

