22:08.291 --> 22:10.542
And the plot thickens,
my friend.

22:22.792 --> 22:25.083
♪ [JAZZ SYMBOLS] ♪

22:25.834 --> 22:27.291
Phoo...

22:28.250 --> 22:31.834
♪ [NOIR MUSIC CONTINUES] ♪

22:35.708 --> 22:37.291
[CLEARS THROAT]

22:43.208 --> 22:46.667
♪ [NOIR MUSIC CONTINUES] ♪

22:51.417 --> 22:52.542
Where're you goin'?

22:53.458 --> 22:55.250
What, are you daft, man?

22:55.250 --> 22:57.166
I'm goin' after her.
That girl is in dire need

22:57.166 --> 22:57.875
of following.

22:58.125 --> 22:59.291
All right. Good.
No, you go follow her.

22:59.291 --> 23:00.917
I'm gonna stay here
and check out that boat.

23:00.917 --> 23:03.458
Sure, now you're
thinkin', butch.

23:04.125 --> 23:08.333
♪ [NOIR MUSIC CONTINUES] ♪

23:11.417 --> 23:13.583
♪ [CYMBALS] ♪

23:19.041 --> 23:22.375
♪ [NOIR MUSIC CONTINUES] ♪

23:30.917 --> 23:32.291
-COP: Hands up!
-[GUN COCKS]

23:32.291 --> 23:33.708
You're under arrest.

23:43.667 --> 23:45.083
Dawson Leery.

23:45.333 --> 23:47.125
Why am I not surprised?

23:47.625 --> 23:48.667
[LAUGHS]

23:48.667 --> 23:51.083
Let me guess: research
for your screenplay.

23:51.083 --> 23:52.750
No, a friend of mine
lives here.

23:53.291 --> 23:54.500
This friend wouldn't,
by any chance,

23:54.500 --> 23:56.625
be your mysterious
femme fatale, would she?

23:56.917 --> 23:57.750
No.

23:58.166 --> 24:01.125
Nothing as lurid as that,
I'm afraid...just a friend.

24:01.583 --> 24:04.583
Aw, funny. Never figured you
for the type to be,

24:04.583 --> 24:06.667
uh, pals with
octogenarians.

24:07.625 --> 24:08.375
Come again?

24:08.792 --> 24:11.083
That boat, on which you were
very much a trespasser,

24:11.083 --> 24:13.834
belongs to a Mr. and
Mrs. Paul Stepmuck.

24:14.375 --> 24:15.250
Sweet little couple.

24:15.250 --> 24:17.375
Somewhere
in their late eighties.

24:18.834 --> 24:19.583
Oh.

24:19.875 --> 24:21.500
Yeah. Oh.

24:23.750 --> 24:27.291
Dawson, the Stepmucks are
big fans of Capeside,

24:27.625 --> 24:29.291
but only in the summertime.

24:29.667 --> 24:31.375
They spend the rest
of their golden year

24:31.375 --> 24:32.500
in New York City.

24:32.500 --> 24:34.291
Heh, well, I...
must have clambered

24:34.291 --> 24:35.750
aboard the wrong boat then.

24:35.750 --> 24:37.500
Maybe you did clamber wrong.

24:38.250 --> 24:39.583
Then again,
maybe your friend

24:39.583 --> 24:41.166
is the one
we've been looking for.

24:41.166 --> 24:42.375
What do you mean?

24:42.375 --> 24:44.166
A couple of weeks ago,
somebody stole a speedboat

24:44.166 --> 24:46.291
from the marina and took
it for a little joyride.

24:48.166 --> 24:49.333
A speedboat, really?

24:49.333 --> 24:50.792
You wouldn't know
anything about that,

24:50.792 --> 24:52.125
would you, Dawson?

24:53.667 --> 24:55.208
No. Heh.

24:55.208 --> 24:56.708
I mean, why would I?

24:57.458 --> 24:59.041
Look, Dawson...

25:00.417 --> 25:02.834
I know that you're a good kid,

25:03.250 --> 25:06.375
but something
is going on with you.

25:07.834 --> 25:11.083
All of a sudden,
you're the boy who cried 911,

25:11.834 --> 25:14.834
you pose thinly
veiled hypotheticals

25:14.834 --> 25:16.417
to an officer of the law,

25:16.834 --> 25:19.959
and all of this
somehow revolves around

25:19.959 --> 25:22.500
some mysterious
femme fatale.

25:23.083 --> 25:25.500
Which, of course,
begs the question...

25:26.375 --> 25:29.250
Is there something you
have to tell me, Dawson?

25:32.125 --> 25:33.792
Deputy Doug in the house!

25:34.083 --> 25:36.834
Ha ha ha!
Oh, I should have known.

25:37.333 --> 25:38.333
Wherever there's smoke,

25:38.333 --> 25:40.000
there's my imbecilic
little brother.

25:40.458 --> 25:44.375
Doug, if I've told you once,
I've told you a million times,

25:44.375 --> 25:46.500
Despite his dapper,
GAP-clad appearance,

25:46.500 --> 25:49.834
my friend Dawson does not
play for your team, ok?

25:50.166 --> 25:51.208
You're just gonna have to find

25:51.208 --> 25:52.792
another date to
the policeman's ball.

25:52.792 --> 25:54.041
Little brother,

25:54.625 --> 25:57.375
your obsession with
my sexuality is just...

25:57.834 --> 25:58.792
plain weird.

25:59.375 --> 26:01.000
Look, do I have to talk
to dad again, huh?

26:01.000 --> 26:02.708
-[CHUCKLES]
-Doug...

26:03.458 --> 26:05.750
It may not be today,
and it may not be tomorrow,

26:05.750 --> 26:07.750
and it might not even be
the day after that,

26:07.750 --> 26:09.041
but one of these days,

26:09.041 --> 26:10.291
you're gonna go
to your mailbox,

26:10.291 --> 26:11.208
you're gonna open it up,

26:11.458 --> 26:13.333
and that Advocate
cover story will be yours...

26:13.834 --> 26:14.875
The copy's gonna read:

26:15.291 --> 26:18.542
"Good Cop/Gay Cop:
The Dougie Witter Story."

26:18.875 --> 26:20.333
And I'm tellin' you, Doug,

26:20.333 --> 26:22.458
we are gonna be
so proud of you.

26:22.708 --> 26:24.208
Really, truly.

26:24.208 --> 26:26.417
[CHUCKLING]

26:26.417 --> 26:27.333
Whew.

26:28.000 --> 26:29.583
I am not gay!

26:30.625 --> 26:33.375
Now, both of you,
off this dock now!

26:33.375 --> 26:34.542
I mean it.

26:35.417 --> 26:37.291
[SUPPRESSING LAUGHTER]

26:38.583 --> 26:39.208
So?

26:39.708 --> 26:41.834
Uh, she's squirrelly, that one.
Lost me like that.

26:42.375 --> 26:43.291
[SIGHS]

26:44.583 --> 26:48.125
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]
-[DOG BARKING]

26:49.875 --> 26:52.166
[VOICES CHATTER]

26:55.083 --> 26:57.875
[CASH REGISTER WINDS]

27:09.542 --> 27:12.208
[VOICES CHATTERING]

27:17.166 --> 27:18.458
Oh, my God, Joey!
[GIGGLES]

27:18.458 --> 27:20.875
What are you doing here?
Oh, it doesn't matter come here.

27:20.875 --> 27:23.625
Isn't this amazing?
Me on a date with Rob Logan,

27:23.625 --> 27:25.458
Senator Logan's son.
I mean, his parents are loaded.

27:25.458 --> 27:27.667
Not that that matters,
but it doesn't hurt either,

27:27.959 --> 27:29.625
and he's so cute.

27:30.000 --> 27:31.959
Slow down, Andie, ok?
Um...

27:32.375 --> 27:34.959
Rob Logan is not a nice guy.

27:35.291 --> 27:36.875
Since I started working for him,

27:36.875 --> 27:39.708
my life has become
one gigantic leer fest.

27:40.458 --> 27:42.792
He's a creep to
an exponential degree.

27:43.291 --> 27:46.458
Ok, Joey, this may come
as a surprise to you,

27:46.458 --> 27:48.500
but not everybody minds
being looked at

27:48.500 --> 27:50.000
as a sexual object.

27:50.875 --> 27:52.834
The guy hits on me daily
in a wide variety

27:52.834 --> 27:55.250
of creative and
not-so-creative ways.

27:55.250 --> 27:58.208
My first day, he walked in on me
while I was changing my clothes.

27:59.375 --> 28:01.166
Why are you trying
to ruin this for me?

28:01.166 --> 28:03.625
Look, I-- I'm not
trying to ruin anything.

28:04.333 --> 28:05.417
I just thought you should know

28:05.417 --> 28:07.500
what kind of a guy
Rob Logan really is.

28:07.875 --> 28:12.834
Uh, Joey, guys is hardly
your area of expertise.

28:12.834 --> 28:15.291
I mean, between Dawson
and my gay brother...

28:15.667 --> 28:17.458
I'm sorry, but it's true.
I mean...

28:17.458 --> 28:19.000
You're not exactly
sophisticated when

28:19.000 --> 28:20.834
it comes to dealing with guys.

28:21.250 --> 28:22.333
[SCOFFS]

28:23.000 --> 28:26.500
Get a grip, ok?
It's-- it's not about me.

28:26.500 --> 28:27.667
Yeah, it is, Joey.

28:27.667 --> 28:29.667
I mean, you're still
fixated on Dawson,

28:30.041 --> 28:32.542
and you're so closed off
to any new experience,

28:32.542 --> 28:35.417
that a guy so much as looks
at you and you freak out.

28:36.083 --> 28:38.417
Joey, staying home
every Friday night

28:38.417 --> 28:39.708
isn't gonna bring him back.

28:39.708 --> 28:41.583
Oh, going out with
a nimrod like Rob Logan

28:41.583 --> 28:43.166
is a recipe
for recovery?

28:44.542 --> 28:46.166
Andie, if you think
this little escapade

28:46.166 --> 28:47.542
is going to help you
get over Pacey--

28:47.542 --> 28:49.583
Joey, I'm moving on
with my life.

28:50.041 --> 28:52.208
Somehow I thought
you, of all people,

28:52.208 --> 28:54.667
would understand that
and be happy for me.

28:58.125 --> 29:00.000
I guess I was wrong.

29:07.458 --> 29:08.583
Excuse me.

29:09.166 --> 29:10.333
Sorry.

29:12.166 --> 29:13.417
I was getting worried.

29:13.834 --> 29:15.917
You missed the previews
and the dancing candy.

29:15.917 --> 29:17.208
Sorry, long line.

29:17.875 --> 29:19.083
This is gonna be great.

29:19.083 --> 29:20.333
Heh heh.

29:21.375 --> 29:22.750
JOEY: Excuse me.

29:23.333 --> 29:25.125
Coming through.
Pardon me.

29:25.750 --> 29:26.792
Sorry.

29:26.792 --> 29:27.959
Sorry.

29:28.583 --> 29:29.500
[CREAKING CHAIRS]

29:29.500 --> 29:31.291
Joey, what are you doing?

29:31.750 --> 29:33.500
These are great seats.

29:33.500 --> 29:34.500
Regular or diet?

29:34.500 --> 29:36.083
I couldn't remember,
so I got both.

29:36.083 --> 29:37.792
No, get out of here. Now.

29:37.792 --> 29:40.667
Mmm. Andie,
in the light of the day

29:40.667 --> 29:42.750
you can psychoanalyze me
all you want,

29:42.750 --> 29:45.250
but I am not leaving you alone
with this guy.

29:46.208 --> 29:47.125
[CANDY FALLS]

29:47.125 --> 29:48.792
What the hell's
going on here, Potter?

29:49.625 --> 29:51.125
Do you like nachos?

29:51.125 --> 29:52.375
Personally, I find them to be

29:52.625 --> 29:55.000
one of the more disgusting
innovations in movie food.

29:55.000 --> 29:56.959
I mean, all this
congealed stuff.

29:56.959 --> 29:58.458
It's not even...
[SNIFFS] cheese.

29:58.458 --> 30:00.542
You know, it's
kind of cheese food.

30:01.125 --> 30:03.000
Here. Try 'em.

30:06.667 --> 30:09.083
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

30:09.542 --> 30:12.542
[CRACKLING CANDY BOX]

30:12.542 --> 30:15.208
Oh, this is comic gold...
This stuff.

30:18.125 --> 30:19.208
Goober?

30:23.583 --> 30:26.208
There's ice cream
in the freezer.

30:28.041 --> 30:29.458
Oh, yeah.

30:29.917 --> 30:31.166
Ever since I started
playing football,

30:31.166 --> 30:33.083
I've been eating you
out of house and home, huh?

30:33.083 --> 30:34.375
No problem.

30:34.834 --> 30:36.333
I just wish
I felt a little more

30:36.333 --> 30:37.875
like I was earning
my keep around here.

30:37.875 --> 30:40.750
But you are. You are making
my granddaughter happy.

30:40.750 --> 30:43.959
Happier than I've seen her
in quite a long while.

30:44.583 --> 30:45.834
[DOOR SLAMS]

30:46.333 --> 30:49.125
Oh, Jennifer, you
scared me half to death.

30:49.125 --> 30:51.333
I'm sorry, Grams.
Getting surprised really sucks,

30:51.333 --> 30:52.458
Doesn't it, Jack?

30:52.708 --> 30:53.667
Jennifer--

30:53.667 --> 30:55.250
This is between Jack and I.

30:56.375 --> 30:57.500
So, how does it work?

30:57.500 --> 30:59.959
Do you take cash,
credit card?

30:59.959 --> 31:01.291
And is it just Henry

31:01.291 --> 31:03.250
or am I gonna have to service
the entire football team?

31:03.250 --> 31:05.041
Jen, calm down.
You're overreacting.

31:05.041 --> 31:06.375
Which one of you
is going to tell me

31:06.375 --> 31:07.750
what's going on here?

31:08.458 --> 31:11.417
I-- I just thought I'd
do a favor for a friend.

31:11.417 --> 31:13.834
So, I set 'em up.
I thought it would be romantic.

31:13.834 --> 31:15.458
About as romantic
as a car-jacking.

31:16.000 --> 31:17.875
Jen, he's just a kid. All right?

31:17.875 --> 31:19.041
He's a nice kid,
and he likes you.

31:19.041 --> 31:20.875
Yeah, he's a real nice kid.
he stares at me

31:20.875 --> 31:22.875
like I'm a pornographic
fantasy come to life.

31:23.125 --> 31:24.625
That's because
he's infatuated with you.

31:24.625 --> 31:26.333
Well, I'm not
infatuated with him.

31:26.333 --> 31:27.708
And I told you that
a thousand times,

31:27.708 --> 31:29.250
and you didn't listen to me.

31:29.250 --> 31:30.250
You took his side.

31:30.250 --> 31:32.708
I didn't take anybody's side.
I-- I--

31:32.708 --> 31:34.750
wanted to get your little
football buddy lucky.

31:36.417 --> 31:37.708
Well, sorry.

31:44.208 --> 31:46.250
♪ [NOIR SAXOPHONE MUSIC] ♪

31:46.250 --> 31:48.041
What the hell are you
doing in my room?

31:48.041 --> 31:49.458
I want my picture back.

31:49.458 --> 31:51.041
And I want some answers.

31:52.250 --> 31:53.291
Fine, Dawson.

31:53.291 --> 31:54.458
What would you like to know?

31:54.458 --> 31:55.875
I'd like to know why
every single word

31:55.875 --> 31:57.333
out of your mouth
has been a lie.

31:57.750 --> 31:59.083
Why you claim to be
a high school student

31:59.083 --> 32:00.583
and you're not.
Why you're living in a yacht

32:00.583 --> 32:01.750
that doesn't belong to you.

32:01.750 --> 32:04.083
I want to know,
once and for all, who you are.

32:06.000 --> 32:08.166
You have every right
to ask those questions, Dawson.

32:08.166 --> 32:10.417
And I promise you,
the answers are forthcoming.

32:10.417 --> 32:12.125
Eve, I'm sick and tired
of being toyed with.

32:12.125 --> 32:14.208
Ever since you slam-danced
your way into my life,

32:14.208 --> 32:15.375
I've wrecked my father's boat--

32:15.375 --> 32:17.542
that was so worth every
penny, and you know it.

32:17.542 --> 32:19.417
It's been one disaster
after another.

32:19.667 --> 32:22.542
I turn a dork into a stud
in a matter of weeks,

32:22.917 --> 32:26.458
and this is my thank you note?
Where's the love?

32:26.458 --> 32:28.750
Eve, the "gee, aren't I so hip
and amoral" routine

32:28.750 --> 32:29.750
is really old.

32:30.291 --> 32:32.041
Is that what you think
I am, amoral?

32:32.041 --> 32:33.250
Either that
or a criminal.

32:33.250 --> 32:35.000
Sticks and stones, Dawson.

32:35.750 --> 32:37.375
Now, give me back my picture.

32:37.375 --> 32:38.500
Eve, for the last time,

32:38.500 --> 32:40.333
what were you doing
in Grams' house?

32:41.125 --> 32:43.041
Looking for something
to steal...

32:43.041 --> 32:44.792
To get bus money
out of here.

32:45.333 --> 32:46.834
There. Satisfied?

32:47.375 --> 32:48.792
Now, give it to me.

32:49.834 --> 32:52.166
Not until you tell me
how a faded, old snapshot

32:52.166 --> 32:55.250
could mean so much to someone
as cold and detached as you.

33:02.000 --> 33:03.458
You're right, Dawson.

33:04.875 --> 33:06.583
I never was a student.

33:08.291 --> 33:09.625
The yacht...

33:10.125 --> 33:13.250
Not mine. I was just
sort of squatting.

33:15.708 --> 33:17.625
And that girl's
my mother, Dawson...

33:18.959 --> 33:20.333
Whom I've never met.

33:21.041 --> 33:22.750
Whom I'm trying
to find...

33:23.917 --> 33:26.125
And that picture
is my only clue.

33:32.667 --> 33:33.917
Talk. I'll listen.

33:34.667 --> 33:37.041
Ok, let's see...
where to begin?

33:38.375 --> 33:39.375
How 'bout last Christmas

33:39.375 --> 33:41.250
as I was rummaging
around in the attic

33:41.625 --> 33:43.166
looking for some
wrapping paper?

33:43.500 --> 33:45.542
I found the photo
in question...

33:46.083 --> 33:48.875
Of the girl that bears
me an uncanny resemblance.

33:49.333 --> 33:50.542
What did you do?

33:51.250 --> 33:53.000
I asked my folks,
of course.

33:53.000 --> 33:54.083
And?

33:55.208 --> 33:56.375
Painted into a corner,

33:56.375 --> 33:58.917
mom and Major Dad
finally told me the truth.

33:59.750 --> 34:01.708
-That you were adopted?
-That's right.

34:02.500 --> 34:04.583
No more calls,
we have a winner.

34:04.959 --> 34:06.208
What did you do?

34:07.041 --> 34:08.166
Nothing.

34:09.208 --> 34:12.250
Very strangely,
I had no angst whatsoever.

34:12.917 --> 34:16.417
It's only after that it kind
of crept up on me that I...

34:17.542 --> 34:20.375
Had this estrogen-charged
urge to seek out

34:20.375 --> 34:21.833
the missing pieces
of the puzzle.

34:21.833 --> 34:23.417
Which brings you
to Capeside. Why?

34:25.000 --> 34:26.750
All I know about
my birth mother is that

34:26.750 --> 34:28.041
she lived somewhere

34:28.041 --> 34:30.083
in this part of the country...
near the ocean.

34:30.083 --> 34:33.000
So, I've been traveling up
and down the eastern seaboard,

34:33.000 --> 34:34.750
asking questions
along the way,

34:35.792 --> 34:38.000
-Hoping to get lucky.
-And have you?

34:40.833 --> 34:42.083
Depends on what you mean.

34:43.542 --> 34:46.250
No, Dawson,
I haven't found her.

34:46.917 --> 34:49.333
Not yet, anyway,
and not here.

34:50.250 --> 34:52.125
Which means it's time
for me to move on...

34:53.375 --> 34:56.250
And so ends another
installment in my melodrama.

34:56.583 --> 34:58.333
It's more movie-of-the-week
than film noir.

34:58.333 --> 34:59.250
With an edge.

34:59.250 --> 35:00.417
With a lot of edge.

35:00.875 --> 35:02.000
Heh.

35:03.250 --> 35:04.750
Oh, I don't know.

35:06.333 --> 35:07.750
Eve, call me gullible, but...

35:09.083 --> 35:10.792
This time I actually
believe you.

35:16.583 --> 35:17.583
[SIGHS]

35:18.583 --> 35:19.667
Thanks, Dawson.

35:21.417 --> 35:23.000
You're a hugely sweet boy.

35:23.583 --> 35:24.792
And you're right,

35:26.166 --> 35:27.792
I played with you.

35:27.792 --> 35:29.125
I do that, I guess.

35:29.667 --> 35:30.834
I move into a new town,

35:30.834 --> 35:32.750
and chances are
I'm not staying forever,

35:33.500 --> 35:34.959
so I play a role.

35:34.959 --> 35:36.917
That way no one
can get close to me.

35:37.166 --> 35:37.917
And believe me,

35:38.291 --> 35:40.041
most guys are content
with me, the actress.

35:42.208 --> 35:43.583
But you dug at me...

35:44.750 --> 35:47.667
You wanted to see inside
my screwed-up little soul.

35:49.583 --> 35:50.917
Well, I mean...

35:51.375 --> 35:52.792
Once you get past the lying,

35:52.792 --> 35:54.458
and the stealing,

35:54.458 --> 35:56.041
and the using sex
as a weapon...

35:56.792 --> 35:57.834
[LAUGHS]

35:58.333 --> 36:00.208
There's a lot of
good stuff in there.

36:02.000 --> 36:04.708
I hope I haven't done
anything irredeemable.

36:06.291 --> 36:07.959
Because I'd like to think
you'll remember me

36:07.959 --> 36:09.667
once in a while and smile.

36:10.667 --> 36:13.291
Well, the ride in
my father's boat alone

36:13.291 --> 36:15.708
will always elicit at least
a giddy grin or three.

36:15.708 --> 36:17.291
See, there you go.

36:18.125 --> 36:19.500
Maybe I'll even get a footnote

36:19.500 --> 36:21.166
in the unauthorized biography.

36:21.542 --> 36:24.417
You just might warrant
a whole chapter.

36:28.792 --> 36:31.458
I'll be checking
the credits for you, Dawson.

36:32.083 --> 36:33.333
Take care, Eve.

36:35.792 --> 36:38.917
♪ [MUSIC] ♪

36:41.083 --> 36:43.375
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

36:48.417 --> 36:50.166
Should I just
fall on my sword now

36:50.166 --> 36:51.750
or wait until
the battle's over?

36:53.708 --> 36:55.000
What do I care?

36:55.000 --> 36:56.667
Either way
you're a dead man.

36:58.792 --> 36:59.959
Look, uh...

37:01.542 --> 37:03.208
This whole
Henry thing...

37:04.083 --> 37:05.208
You got it
all wrong, ok?

37:05.208 --> 37:07.583
I didn't do it for him.
I did it for you.

37:09.166 --> 37:10.333
I'm serious.

37:11.417 --> 37:13.333
I-- I-- I just wanted
to show you

37:13.333 --> 37:17.041
that the things that you want
are there for the taking,

37:17.500 --> 37:20.125
if you just, you know, believe
you deserve them.

37:21.542 --> 37:22.750
You don't get it.

37:23.583 --> 37:24.667
This was our place.

37:25.458 --> 37:26.417
Yours and mine.

37:26.417 --> 37:27.875
Doesn't that mean
something to you?

37:27.875 --> 37:29.125
Yeah, of course it does...

37:29.708 --> 37:31.792
But... don't you want more?

37:32.166 --> 37:34.834
No. Not from us.

37:38.375 --> 37:39.667
Jack...

37:40.208 --> 37:42.166
I've had lovers,
I've had boyfriends,

37:42.166 --> 37:45.250
but-- but what I've
never had is a boy

37:45.917 --> 37:48.208
who is, first and last,
a friend...

37:49.166 --> 37:51.500
Who wasn't secretly
trying to get in my pants

37:51.500 --> 37:53.625
or wouldn't
walk away from me

37:53.625 --> 37:55.500
the second I said I didn't
want to sleep with him...

37:55.500 --> 37:59.625
Who liked me...for me.

38:03.667 --> 38:06.375
Unless you've recently
decided to be bisexual.

38:06.708 --> 38:08.041
[LAUGHS]

38:10.708 --> 38:12.291
You know, I think that
you setting me up

38:12.291 --> 38:14.458
was a lot more about you
than it was me.

38:15.500 --> 38:17.166
Come on,
give me a break.

38:17.166 --> 38:20.959
I do not have a secret crush
on Henry Parker.

38:20.959 --> 38:23.166
Neither do I, but that's not
what I'm talking about.

38:25.375 --> 38:29.708
I mean, maybe it's you who's
lonely for the relationship.

38:35.000 --> 38:36.708
Well, maybe I am.

38:38.625 --> 38:40.208
But this isn't exactly New York,

38:40.208 --> 38:42.417
where gay kids are
tripping over each other

38:42.417 --> 38:43.500
comin' out of the closet.

38:43.500 --> 38:44.875
This is Capeside.

38:44.875 --> 38:46.583
Gay population is one.

38:47.625 --> 38:48.834
It's me. I'm it.

38:48.834 --> 38:49.917
Jack...

38:52.166 --> 38:54.208
You're gonna have a love life.

38:54.792 --> 38:56.875
You're gonna have
a fantastic love life,

38:56.875 --> 39:01.917
and it's gonna be...
awesome and terrifying and--

39:02.959 --> 39:04.500
and when it happens,
it's gonna change

39:04.500 --> 39:05.792
your whole life.

39:08.834 --> 39:10.625
Yeah, it's easy
for you to say.

39:11.250 --> 39:12.542
I know it is.

39:14.917 --> 39:16.083
You just--

39:16.708 --> 39:18.333
you have to have faith...

39:19.125 --> 39:22.250
That sometimes things happen
when they're least expected.

39:25.750 --> 39:27.917
-[WATER SPRAYS]
-♪ [MUSIC] ♪

39:29.333 --> 39:30.792
See what I mean?

39:31.500 --> 39:33.291
[LAUGHING]

39:35.500 --> 39:37.125
-Whoo!
-Whaa!

39:48.208 --> 39:49.667
-Hey.
-Hi.

39:49.667 --> 39:51.500
Uh, stud puppy's
not here yet.

39:52.375 --> 39:54.500
You must have kept him out
pretty late last night.

39:54.500 --> 39:56.250
Ok, nothing happened.

39:56.792 --> 39:58.834
And not that you
deserve an explanation,

39:58.834 --> 40:01.458
but right after the movie,
he walked me to my front door,

40:01.458 --> 40:02.750
and he was
a perfect gentleman.

40:03.125 --> 40:04.458
Yeah, he's a prince,
all right...

40:04.792 --> 40:06.500
Prince of Darkness.

40:06.875 --> 40:07.875
Hey, Rob.

40:08.375 --> 40:10.000
Slackin' off
on the job again, Potter?

40:10.542 --> 40:13.542
Uh, you know, Joey and I
just...girl talk.

40:13.542 --> 40:14.875
-[LAUGHS]
-Yeah, I know.

40:15.250 --> 40:17.375
So, last night,
quite a threesome...

40:17.625 --> 40:19.500
Only next time I want
to be in the middle.

40:20.417 --> 40:22.083
It was kind of an
unexpected pleasure though.

40:22.083 --> 40:23.500
I mean, I assumed
you were working.

40:24.000 --> 40:25.917
Don't we usually stay open
till 8:00 on Fridays?

40:26.250 --> 40:28.667
Nobody ever comes in after 7:00.
You know that, Rob.

40:29.291 --> 40:30.959
Just answer
the question, Potter.

40:31.708 --> 40:32.583
[SCOFFS]

40:34.875 --> 40:37.458
Yeah, we usually stay open
until 8:00 on Fridays.

40:38.250 --> 40:39.291
You're fired.

40:41.041 --> 40:42.250
What?!

40:42.250 --> 40:43.417
You heard me.

40:43.750 --> 40:45.250
I'm in charge here,
and it's unacceptable

40:45.250 --> 40:47.583
for an employee to close early
without my permission.

40:47.583 --> 40:50.083
Oh, yeah, and that's really
why you're firing me, Rob.

40:50.375 --> 40:52.166
Spare me the adolescent
mini-drama, Potter.

40:52.417 --> 40:54.208
You're fired
because you closed early.

40:54.208 --> 40:55.166
End of story.

40:55.625 --> 40:58.959
No, wait, Joey.
um, she can explain.

40:58.959 --> 40:59.959
I mean, this is all

40:59.959 --> 41:01.333
just a really big
misunderstanding.

41:01.708 --> 41:03.041
Look, don't bother,
Andie.

41:04.041 --> 41:05.500
Nice workin' with ya, Potter.

41:08.166 --> 41:09.417
You know what, Rob?

41:09.708 --> 41:11.125
The day your
out-of-whack libido

41:11.125 --> 41:13.083
lands you in so deep
that not even daddy

41:13.083 --> 41:14.125
can save your ass,

41:14.834 --> 41:16.625
don't call me as
a character witness.

41:18.208 --> 41:19.375
Rot in hell.

41:23.750 --> 41:26.625
♪ [MUSIC] ♪

41:32.375 --> 41:33.875
Oh, my word.

41:33.875 --> 41:36.417
Beware of heretics
bearing air conditioners.

41:37.667 --> 41:39.250
[SIGH]
My father's orders.

41:39.750 --> 41:41.917
He wanted me to take this extra
of ours over to you.

41:43.917 --> 41:45.208
[DOOR CREAKS]

41:45.959 --> 41:46.959
[SIGHS]

41:52.625 --> 41:53.708
[THUD]

41:55.625 --> 41:57.708
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

42:06.542 --> 42:08.500
Mrs. Ryan, who is that
in that picture?

42:08.917 --> 42:10.708
Well, that's our Lord,
Jesus Christ,

42:10.708 --> 42:12.792
as interpreted
by one of our gifted,

42:12.792 --> 42:14.667
young Sunday School students.

42:14.667 --> 42:15.959
I meant the one
below it.

42:16.500 --> 42:17.583
Oh...

42:18.166 --> 42:19.542
That's my daughter, Helen.

42:19.834 --> 42:21.417
She can't have been more
than 18 there.

42:21.417 --> 42:24.375
As I recall, it was right before
she went away to college.

42:27.000 --> 42:28.291
So, that's Jen's mom?

42:28.834 --> 42:31.250
I have only one daughter,
Dawson Leery.

42:36.041 --> 42:38.708
♪ [MUSIC] ♪
